Sassasras montana was described by Brown for specimens from the Hell Creek formation of Montana, as follows:

“Leaves 8 00111111101013 or more wide, three-lobed, the lobes relatively short, blunt-rounded; sinuses narrow, rounded; base cuneate; petiole 5 centimeters long.
